A patient has certain details like name, phone_no, camp_id, consultation_history (which contains the list of previous doctor visits from the camp), sex, height, weight, etc. The patient needs to go through certain steps before each consultation. 1. register and get the token. 2. general consultation where height and general stats are collected. 3.doctor consultation. 4. prescribed checkup (eye check up, thyroid checkup etc.) 5. give samples for tests. 6. get prescribed drugs and medical aids. No fee is collected from the patient, since it's being sponsored for the underprivileged sector. A volunteer is assigned at every stage of the process and doesn't have access to modify other details except for that stage.<br></div><div><b><br></b></div><div><b>Relations</b></div><div>A patient, a volunteer, a doctor can attend one or more medical camps</div><div>A doctor attends to one or more consultation, but a consultation can have 0 doctors (general tests and vital checkup)</div><div>A patient receives one or more consultations</div><div>A consultation generates zero or more reports or prescribes zero or more drug prescription.&nbsp;</div><div>Both drug prescription and report needs to have a consultation associated with them</div><div><br></div><div><br></div>" div.div: A medical camp is conducted every first Sunday of the month. A patient has certain details like name, phone_no, camp_id, consultation_history (which contains the list of previous doctor visits from the camp), sex, height, weight, etc. The patient needs to go through certain steps before each consultation. 1. register and get the token. 2. general consultation where height and general stats are collected. 3.doctor consultation. 4. prescribed checkup (eye check up, thyroid checkup etc.) 5. give samples for tests. 6. get prescribed drugs and medical aids. No fee is collected from the patient, since it's being sponsored for the underprivileged sector. A volunteer is assigned at every stage of the process and doesn't have access to modify other details except for that stage.
A patient, a volunteer, a doctor can attend one or more medical camps
A doctor attends to one or more consultation, but a consultation can have 0 doctors (general tests and vital checkup)
A patient receives one or more consultations
A consultation generates zero or more reports or prescribes zero or more drug prescription.Â
Both drug prescription and report needs to have a consultation associated with them
